    <title>Is possible to combine multiple views with single table mode in OData V2 Fiori List Report?</title>
    <updated>2025-02-26T16:41:33.793000+01:00</updated>
    <author>
      <name>catalinfeidi</name>
      <uri>https://community.sap.com/t5/user/viewprofilepage/user-id/151918</uri>
    </author>
    <content>&lt;P&gt;Hi,&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;While in OData V4 is possible, I'm wondering if there is a possibility to do it also in OData V2 for Fiori List Report since there is no documentation on how to achieve it on OData V2 List Report.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&lt;span class="lia-inline-image-display-wrapper lia-image-align-inline" image-alt="catalinfeidi_0-1740584169026.png" style="width: 400px;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://community.sap.com/t5/image/serverpage/image-id/230726iBFFDF4531E149D3F/image-size/medium?v=v2&amp;amp;px=400" role="button" title="catalinfeidi_0-1740584169026.png" alt="catalinfeidi_0-1740584169026.png" /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;I could just find on UI5 Doc &lt;A href="https://ui5.sap.com//#/topic/37aeed74e17a42caa2cba3123f0c15fc" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"&gt;https://ui5.sap.com//#/topic/37aeed74e17a42caa2cba3123f0c15fc&lt;/A&gt;&amp;nbsp;, but only on OData V4 section (&lt;EM&gt;"you can combine multiple views with quick filters (single table mode). You can configure each table in themanifest.json&amp;nbsp;in the&amp;nbsp;controlConfiguration&amp;nbsp;and define the&amp;nbsp;quickvariantSelection&lt;/EM&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;&lt;EM&gt;&amp;nbsp;for a table."&lt;/EM&gt;)&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&lt;SPAN&gt;I tried to add the selectionvariant to tableSettings, since just there I could see, because in list report odata v2 based there is no controlConfiguration...and still the single tabs are not appearing.&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;Is this a limitation for odata v2 list report?&lt;/P&gt;</content>
    <link href="https://community.sap.com/t5/technology-q-a/is-possible-to-combine-multiple-views-with-single-table-mode-in-odata-v2/qaq-p/14028438"/>
    <published>2025-02-26T16:41:33.793000+01:00</published>
  </entry>
