    <content>&lt;P&gt;I want to display a user's SuccessFactors to-do list as notifications in a Fiori application.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;I am fetching data via the SuccessFactors API, and the response contains dynamic navigation links for each to-do task. In my requirement for a notification app, when a user clicks on a notification, it should navigate to the corresponding SuccessFactors task link.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;My question is: How do I assign these dynamic links, fetched from the SuccessFactors API, to each notification?&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;While creating notifications, we define navigation properties, but I suppose that only works for static links.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;To create notifications, I am using the CREATE_NOTIFICATIONS method of the class /IWNGW/CL_NOTIFICATION_API. I have also created a notification provider class that inherits from the /IWNGW/IF_NOTIF_PROVIDER interface.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;Any guidance on how to achieve this would be greatly appreciated!&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;</content>
